<appendix xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
  version="5.0">
  <title>Documentation quality</title>
  <para>To increase the quality and consistency of your documentation, use the following
    checklist:</para>
  <informaltable>
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <thead>
        <row>
          <entry>Quality checks</entry>
          <entry>&check;</entry>
        </row>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry>Find all typos in documentation.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Find all typos in code examples.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Eliminate jargon.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Expand contractions.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Simplify phrasal verbs.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Find missing serial commas.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Replace passive voice with active voice.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Eliminate dangling modifiers.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Write in complete sentences.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Use parallel construction within headers.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Change extraneous ordered lists.<footnote>
              <para>Often, it is tempting to use an ordered list in places where an unordered list
                is appropriate, such as a list of three platforms on which to install software.
                Leave it up to the reader to count, and in this example use an unordered
                list.</para>
            </footnote></entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
        <row>
          <entry>Omit gendered language where possible.</entry>
          <entry/>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>
</appendix>
